Digital-Asset Law Corpus — Licence
==================================

Two layers, licensed differently. Read this together with NOTICE.

1. THE DERIVED / COMPILATION LAYER  →  CC BY 4.0
   The selection, arrangement and coordination of the corpus, the structural
   parsing (derived/**/structure.json), the neutral concept tags
   (derived/**/concepts.json, derived/concept-index.json) and the metadata
   schema are licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International
   licence (SPDX: CC-BY-4.0). Full text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode
   You may share and adapt these with attribution (see CITATION.cff).

2. THE SOURCE TEXTS  →  NOT RELICENSED; each keeps its own terms
   The authoritative texts (authoritative/**/text.txt) and the byte-exact
   official originals (authoritative/**/original.*) are official legal
   instruments reproduced from their official sources. They are NOT relicensed
   by this project. Each record's own terms are recorded in its metadata.yaml
   `license` / `rights_note` fields and summarised per record in NOTICE. Only
   records whose reuse terms are confirmed clean (statutory non-copyright,
   government public-domain, or an explicit attribution/open licence) are
   included in this public release; 57 of the corpus's 70 records qualify.

NO LEGAL ADVICE. This is a reference record, not legal or compliance advice.
The authoritative text of each instrument is the official original in its
authentic language; translations and concept tags are unofficial and derived.
Always confirm against the cited official source for anything legally operative.
